      <biogHist id="md5-f943fb447f70dc34cf5f44c7682e258a">
        <p>Petroleum engineer, 1915-1985.  Mr. Adkins, a graduate in Chemical Engineering from the  University of Alberta in 1937, was the superintendent responsible for the design and construction of  the Bitumount oil sands extraction plant.  In association with Born Engineering Company he built refineries throughout Western Canada, including a facility in Turner Valley, Alberta.  In 1946 he  was appointed superintendent of the Alberta Government Oil Sands Project, to build and operate a  demonstration plant at Bitumount.</p>
      </biogHist>
